---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [
  { href: "#latest", label: "Latest" },
  { href: "#archive", label: "Topics" },
  { href: "#about", label: "About" },
];
const navCta = { href: "#subscribe", label: "Subscribe →" };
---

<Layout variant="flagship-observability">
  <Nav variant="flagship-observability" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="masthead-label">Phidea</div>
      <h1>What's actually happening with AI in regulated industries. <em>Weekly.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Every Tuesday morning: the regulator moves, the model updates, the industry experiments, and the ones that didn't make it past compliance review. Written for people who read the primary texts before they read the keynote slides. Insurance-depth first; banking, pharma, and health in the pipeline.
      </p>

      <form action="https://buttondown.email/api/emails/embed-subscribe/phidea" method="POST" class="signup">
        <input type="hidden" name="tag" value="flagship-observability" />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe →</button>
      </form>
      <p class="signup-small">One email per week. Unsubscribe in one click. No sales pitch.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section id="latest" class="latest">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Recent briefs</div>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Compliance</div>
        <h3>Colorado's SB21-169 filings: the first public read on whether a codified quantitative test works at operational cadence.</h3>
        <p>Colorado is the first US state to codify a specific quantitative methodology for AI bias testing in insurance. Carriers file under the rule; the filings are public. The newsletter reads each as it lands and tracks what the pattern signals for every other state adopting the NAIC framework.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Model operations</div>
        <h3>Silent model updates. Why version numbers are not enough for LLM monitoring.</h3>
        <p>Model providers ship behaviour changes between version numbers. Detection requires fixed-prompt probes run on a cadence, not release-note monitoring. The newsletter tracks provider changes and behavioural shifts as they land.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="brief">
        <div class="brief-meta">Topic · Distribution</div>
        <h3>A custom AI agent in a regulated line: the three compliance questions that always come up.</h3>
        <p>Distribution-law advice-boundary (IDD, state producer-licensing), price accuracy, and consumer-disclosure injection. Each has a known runtime solution. The newsletter covers which carriers are shipping, which are stuck on which question, and what the workable patterns look like.</p>
      </article>

      <p class="latest-more"><a href="#archive">See all topics</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="archive" class="archive">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Topics we cover</div>
      <h2>Short reference pages, anchored to primary sources.</h2>
      <p class="archive-lead">
        Each page links the regulations, provider documentation, and academic references that matter for one question. Insurance is where the depth currently sits. The framework expands to banking, pharma, and health over time.
      </p>

      <div class="tier-grid">
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Distribution &amp; AI surfaces</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/ai-visibility.html">When a carrier isn't cited by ChatGPT</a></li>
            <li><a href="/competitor-share.html">The competitor cited instead of you</a></li>
            <li><a href="/custom-gpt.html">A Custom GPT your compliance team can sign off on</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ai-channel.html">Count the business AI assistants send you</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ai-attribution.html">Trace each AI conversation to the policy it bound</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Operations &amp; monitoring</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/ai-monitoring.html">Observability for AI agents in production</a></li>
            <li><a href="/model-drift.html">Catch vendor model updates before a customer does</a></li>
            <li><a href="/hallucination-guardrail.html">Stop a made-up coverage answer before delivery</a></li>
            <li><a href="/audit-bundle.html">Have a regulator bundle ready</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Compliance &amp; governance</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/regulator-mapping.html">Six AI rulebooks, one mapping</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ais-program.html">The AIS Program regulators expect</a></li>
            <li><a href="/adverse-decision-trail.html">Explain every adverse AI decision, statutorily</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ecdis-oversight.html">Track every third-party data source your models touch</a></li>
            <li><a href="/bias-testing.html">Protected-class testing, per jurisdiction</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tier">
          <div class="tier-label">Model risk &amp; actuarial</div>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/mrm-llms.html">MRM extended to LLMs</a></li>
            <li><a href="/predictive-monitoring.html">Watch pricing drift between reserves reviews</a></li>
            <li><a href="/augmented-underwriting.html">Give underwriters their three hours back</a></li>
            <li><a href="/portfolio-drift.html">See portfolio drift before the quarterly deck</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="subscribe" class="subscribe-strip">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Phidea Weekly</div>
      <h2>One email. Every Tuesday. Free.</h2>
      <p>Written for people who have to make the call by Friday.</p>
      <form action="https://buttondown.email/api/emails/embed-subscribe/phidea" method="POST" class="signup">
        <input type="hidden" name="tag" value="flagship-observability" />
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required />
        <button type="submit">Subscribe →</button>
      </form>
      <p class="signup-small">Unsubscribe in one click. No sales pitch. No sponsored content.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="about-strip">
    <div class="wrap wrap-narrow">
      <div class="section-label">Who writes this</div>
      <p>Phidea is a small team tracking AI in regulated industries across firms, platforms, and regulators. We work with a handful of firms on AI governance and publish publicly what we see across the rest of the field. No guest posts. No ghost-writing. No sponsored content.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .wrap-narrow { max-width: 680px; padding-left: 24px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .masthead {
    padding: 96px 0 64px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .masthead-label {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .masthead h1 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 52px;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .masthead h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .masthead .lead {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }

  .signup {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 520px;
  }
  .signup input[type=email] {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .signup button {
    padding: 14px 24px;
    border: none;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: inherit;
  }
  .signup button:hover { background: var(--accent); }
  .signup-small {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .latest { padding: 72px 0 48px; }
  .brief {
    padding: 28px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .brief:first-of-type { padding-top: 8px; }
  .brief:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
  .brief-meta {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .brief h3 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .brief p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .latest-more {
    margin-top: 32px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .latest-more a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .latest-more a:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  .archive {
    padding: 72px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--soft);
  }
  .archive h2 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .archive-lead {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .tier-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
  }
  .tier {
    padding: 20px 24px;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 14px;
  }
  .tier-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .tier ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tier li {
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .tier li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .tier li a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.45;
    display: block;
  }
  .tier li a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .subscribe-strip {
    padding: 96px 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .subscribe-strip .section-label { justify-content: center; display: inline-block; }
  .subscribe-strip h2 {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 40px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .subscribe-strip p {
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 17px;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
  }
  .subscribe-strip .signup { margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }

  .about-strip {
    padding: 72px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--soft);
  }
  .about-strip p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .masthead h1 { font-size: 34px; }
    .masthead .lead { font-size: 17px; }
    .signup { flex-direction: column; }
    .brief h3 { font-size: 20px; }
    .tier-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .archive h2 { font-size: 28px; }
    .subscribe-strip h2 { font-size: 28px; }
  }
</style>
